Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.31,0:00:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.25,0:00:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.50,0:00:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.80,0:00:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.31,0:00:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.27,0:00:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.16,0:01:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.29,0:01:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.02,0:01:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Varon, even though you were the enemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.98,0:01:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...you were also one of the best Duelists I've ever encountered.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.28,0:01:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We really fought with all our might in our Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.55,0:01:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mai, even if it's you, I won't allow anyone to belittle him!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.17,0:01:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come on over here, Mai.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.10,0:01:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We won't be able to understand each other if we don't battle one-on-one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.48,0:01:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I won't try to escape anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.83,0:01:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This time, I'll put in all my best and battle with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.09,0:02:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Bitter Victory"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi! Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.76,0:02:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.19,0:02:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.83,0:02:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! That barrier did appear somewhere around here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.73,0:02:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must be nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.48,0:02:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not give up and continue searching for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.16,0:02:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.01,0:02:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.53,0:02:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to win just by numbers alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.05,0:02:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.55,0:02:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get rid of all this trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.45,0:02:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.05,0:02:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they coming out from?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.13,0:02:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They keep appearing, Big Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.16,0:03:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many there may be, trash will always be trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.44,0:03:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're hardly a match against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.07,0:03:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.78,0:03:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.10,0:03:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You filthy scum!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.31,0:03:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go forth, Critias!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.70,0:03:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.53,0:03:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.57,0:03:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These weak small fries keep coming one by one!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.56,0:03:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes! Critias!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.51,0:03:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eliminate them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.43,0:04:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.15,0:04:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Swordsman of Landstar in Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.02,0:04:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I set two reverse cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.19,0:04:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...two face-down...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.88,0:04:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My vision is getting worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.82,0:04:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The damage I took earlier was no joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.95,0:04:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But... it's too early!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.11,0:04:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were talking so big and mighty before...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.42,0:04:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't you about to collapse, Jounouchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.02,0:04:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.96,0:04:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.69,0:04:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.87,0:04:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when you're facing formidable opponents...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.82,0:04:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how hopeless the situation may appear to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.40,0:04:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you'll never give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.38,0:04:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you afraid of losing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.82,0:05:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.69,0:05:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.41,0:05:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does winning mean to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.74,0:05:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is winning just about defeating your opponents during a Duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.56,0:05:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.62,0:05:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remembered you mentioned about how you can't trust others...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.30,0:05:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That you only trust yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.55,0:05:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But after fighting side by side at Duelist Kingdom..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.57,0:05:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't we all found something more important than winning?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.91,0:05:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.14,0:05:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why have you gone back to fighting on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.20,0:05:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.32,0:05:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.53,0:05:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Always!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong! You're our friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.67,0:05:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.13,0:05:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late! I can only keep fighting now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.93,0:05:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.27,0:05:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough of this pointless conversation!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.74,0:05:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only want to defeat you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.44,0:05:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.02,0:05:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.57,0:06:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I believe in the Mai back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.16,0:06:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will accept your feelings!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.28,0:06:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.76,0:06:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.97,0:06:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.37,0:06:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Harpy Lady to attack Swordsman of Landstar!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.94,0:06:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.97,0:06:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card open!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.27,0:06:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Double Magical Arm Bind!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.11,0:06:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By sacrificing two Monsters on my field, this Trap Card...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.10,0:06:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...can take control of two Monsters on the opponent's field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.84,0:06:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I still have Harpies on my field!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go and attack, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.80,0:06:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it! I still have another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.62,0:06:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card open!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.02,0:06:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vow of Tribe!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.92,0:06:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this card is activated...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.73,0:06:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...if both players have the same number of Monsters on their fields, none of us can battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.58,0:06:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This means that in this turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.16,0:06:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because two Harpy Ladies are on my side of the field... you can't attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:06:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The battle ends!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.73,0:06:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.25,0:07:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to slowly grow up through the course of Dueling...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.19,0:07:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's how I came to be where I am now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.66,0:07:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That spirit is Jounouchi's strong point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.25,0:07:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No matter what kind of mess he may be in...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.62,0:07:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How hopeless the whole situation may be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.20,0:07:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He'll never give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.47,0:07:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't have that in me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.70,0:07:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I finally understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.46,0:07:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why you're so bent on pursuing Jounouchi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.29,0:07:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He holds something we don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You know what it is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.09,0:07:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To face one another in a Duel...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.84,0:07:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...with a genuine straight-forward passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.72,0:07:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't... have that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.39,0:07:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.64,0:07:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, when I defeat you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.94,0:07:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...you will see the true strength I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.11,0:07:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A strength that nobody else has!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.52,0:07:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.72,0:08:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mai.. I feel it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.04,0:08:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your soul as a Duelist has nothing to do with Doma.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.63,0:08:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You just simply want to continue Dueling until your soul is content.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.60,0:08:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.89,0:08:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As a Duelist... I will Duel with you till the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.48,0:08:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.40,0:08:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.24,0:08:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice the two Harpy Ladies I got from you and my Swordsman of Landstar...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.52,0:08:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sacrificing three Monsters?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, Gilford the Lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.91,0:08:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because three Monsters were sacrificed when Gilford the Lightning was Summoned...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.42,0:08:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He will destroy all the Monsters on the opponent's field!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.51,0:09:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I'll use Gilford the Lightning to Direct Attack the opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.70,0:09:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stand up, Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.25,0:09:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our Duel is not over!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.67,0:09:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've definitely become stronger, Jounouchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.79,0:09:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But {\i1}I'm{\i0} the one who will win!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.41,0:09:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.48,0:09:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.88,0:10:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.13,0:10:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Magic Card from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.60,0:10:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Treasure from Heaven!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.46,0:10:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We both can draw until we have six cards in our hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.58,0:10:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better draw too, Jounouchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.20,0:10:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get that card?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.77,0:10:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even though I didn't get Hermos, I did get a pretty good card.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.71,0:10:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if Jounouchi got the Hermos card, I'll defeat him before he gets to use it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.22,0:10:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.07,0:10:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.25,0:10:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revive, Harpy Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.24,0:10:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, another Magic Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.17,0:10:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Kaleidoscope - Magnificent Replication!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.44,0:10:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card allows me to Special Summon Harpy Lady Replicas!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.44,0:11:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She Summoned three Harpy Ladies in just one turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.37,0:11:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That card must be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.09,0:11:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.21,0:11:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.25,0:11:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.03,0:11:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Phoenix Formation!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.09,0:11:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Phoenix Formation allows me to destroy the same number of Monsters my opponent controls as the number of Harpy Ladies I have,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.54,0:11:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and also inflict damage equal to the total Attack Power of the destroyed Monsters to the opponent's Life Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.46,0:11:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, my Harpy Ladies!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.06,0:11:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I got hit...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.33,0:11:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that? My Harpy Combo is flawless.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.03,0:11:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-As I expected, Mai.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.70,0:11:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You took my Life Points down this much in a single turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.68,0:12:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have the energy to talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.44,0:12:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.48,0:12:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a waste if our Duel ends just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.19,0:12:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a True Duelist that I recognize.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.18,0:12:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's more enjoyable than Dueling you with my all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.73,0:12:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.37,0:12:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.00,0:12:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Damn... Just a bit more..!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.22,0:12:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just a little longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.66,0:12:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For Mai's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.27,0:12:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hermos...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.85,0:12:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please give me the last burst of power!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.89,0:12:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card, Warrior's Return!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.85,0:12:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the effect, a Warrior-Type Monster gets revived from the Graveyard into my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.59,0:12:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Blue Flame Swordsman in Attack Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.79,0:13:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next from my hand, I activate a Ritual Magic Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.34,0:13:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Descent of Dark Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.72,0:13:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ritual Magic?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.68,0:13:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By sacrificing Iron Knight Gearfried from my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.40,0:13:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Knight of Dark Dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.00,0:13:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next I activate its Special Ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.84,0:13:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By sacrificing Knight of Dark Dragons...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can Special Summon Red-Eyes Black Dragon from my deck or from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.17,0:13:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appear, Red-Eyes Black Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.40,0:13:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... You can't attack on the same turn when a Monster is Specially Summoned!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.46,0:13:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.66,0:13:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'll activate this card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.76,0:13:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claw of Hermos!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.57,0:13:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By fusing Hermos with Red-Eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.04,0:14:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I equip Red-Eyes Black Dragon Sword on Blue Flame Swordsman!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.13,0:14:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its Attack goes up by 1000 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.53,0:14:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Blue Flame Swordsman!\N Attack Harpy Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.62,0:14:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set two reverse cards and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not yet... it's not over..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.27,0:14:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just a little more...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.71,0:14:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.61,0:14:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how strong the Equipment Card may be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.53,0:14:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it will be nothing once I destroy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.11,0:14:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate a Magic Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.30,0:14:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Harpy's Feather Duster!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With its decreased Attack Points, I can now defeat Blue Flame Swordsman with ease...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.10,0:14:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I can even attack Jounouchi directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.77,0:14:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.63,0:15:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now that it's boiled down to this.. I want to defeat you with all my might!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card! Magic Reproduction!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.42,0:15:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this card, in exchange for discarding two Magic Cards from my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.87,0:15:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can return a Magic Card from the Graveyard back into my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.97,0:15:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The card that you want to get back into your hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.85,0:15:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is Phoenix Formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.93,0:15:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.12,0:15:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to use all my power to defeat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.70,0:15:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Harpy Lady Phoenix Formation!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.58,0:15:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will inflict damage equal to the total Attack of the destroyed Monsters to the your Life Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.55,0:15:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Zero Attack Power?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.25,0:15:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because I've activated the Special Ability of Blue Flame Swordsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.81,0:15:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue Flame Swordsman can transfer its Attack Power to another Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.79,0:15:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've transferred its Attack Power to my {\i1}Harpy{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.70,0:15:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I've transferred it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.49,0:15:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Blue Flame Swordsman has zero Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.16,0:15:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which also means that I took zero damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.89,0:15:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, when Blue Flame Swordsman is destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.90,0:15:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Flame Swordsman will be Specially Summoned onto the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.93,0:16:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To avoid taking any damage in this turn, you've transferred your Attack Power to the enemy's Monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.15,0:16:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you {\i1}thinking{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.21,0:16:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to say that I'm stupid right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.54,0:16:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the same way too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.58,0:16:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is all that I can do right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.08,0:16:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to make you remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.92,0:16:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this Duel, I'll make you remember what is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.96,0:16:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be relying on your own strength to Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.63,0:16:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And not depending on Doma for power!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.20,0:16:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that you're a really gentle person.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.11,0:16:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.72,0:16:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't returned it back to you yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.61,0:16:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless to try to sway my determination by saying all that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.32,0:16:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.05,0:16:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to take the first step, Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.54,0:16:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If not, you'll continue living in pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.50,0:17:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.87,0:17:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.92,0:17:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.76,0:17:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my only choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.23,0:17:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.41,0:17:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn. Draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.41,0:17:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one reverse card...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.14,0:17:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.25,0:17:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.12,0:17:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Harpy Lady Cyber Bondage to attack Flame Swordsman!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.12,0:17:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the end, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.85,0:17:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.86,0:17:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Devil Dice!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.39,0:17:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Harpy Lady's Attack Points are cut in half.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.72,0:17:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I'll still win!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.21,0:18:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll lose once I use Harpy to Direct Attack you next!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.12,0:18:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Harpy! Strike Jounouchi...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.15,0:18:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.23,0:18:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why am I hesitating?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.60,0:18:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's obvious that I'm going to win...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.15,0:18:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You win... Mai...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.79,0:18:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.62,0:19:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.74,0:19:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During your battle with Varon, you were already...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.29,0:19:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.24,0:19:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to see your face anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.21,0:19:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You Dueled with me when you were already in such a bad state...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.38,0:19:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.96,0:19:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't do anything for you in the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.93,0:19:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm glad that your soul isn't going to be taken away...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.27,0:19:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Duel... was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.82,0:19:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,NO!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.30,0:19:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.88,0:19:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The winner is Mai Kujaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.52,0:19:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.85,0:19:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.08,0:19:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Timaeus...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.22,0:20:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Critias is... crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.74,0:20:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.54,0:20:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... No! Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.28,0:20:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it all along!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.86,0:20:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that winning wouldn't change a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.71,0:20:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.20,0:20:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That even if you win...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.88,0:20:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.67,0:20:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can I gain by sacrificing you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dartz...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.60,0:20:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll end it all with {\i1}you{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.01,0:20:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please wait, Jounouchi... Varon...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.53,0:21:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will get your souls back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.33,0:21:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.10,0:21:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.77,0:21:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can this be!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.05,0:21:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.27,0:22:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.63,0:22:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.24,0:22:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.31,0:22:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.79,0:22:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.07,0:22:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.97,0:22:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.12,0:23:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.64,0:23:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.06,0:23:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be true that Jounouchi lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.22,0:23:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that guy Varon's soul was also taken away...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.86,0:23:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This means that Mai-{\i1}san{\i0} was the one that took away Jounouchi's soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.25,0:23:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.60,0:23:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With a sorrowful heart, Yugi enters Paradias alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.37,0:23:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what he sees...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.03,0:23:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is Mai-{\i1}san{\i0} with her soul taken!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.99,0:23:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could have done that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.31,0:23:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.10,0:23:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Duel of Destiny! Yugi vs. Rafael"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.22,0:23:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
